room_description:
The roaring 1920â€™s were filled with crime, seduction and scandal. Liquor was illegal and the famous clubs and bars were just as hard to find. You and a group of undercover agents have been tasked to infiltrate a Speakeasy owned by the notorious gangster, Al Capone. He and his cohorts have been smuggling liquor underground throughout the city of Chicago, and running hidden clubs and casinos behind closed doors of auto parts stores and tailor shops.
Tensions are high among his crew, as they have been tipped off about a mole within their circle. A meeting has been called to discuss the deceit. You and your team have one hour to extract the evidence you need and get out alive, before you are all trapped inside to meet your maker!
